description: If President Andrzej Duda loses, the opposition could force a change in Polish politics.
title: Poland's clash of values in presidential election
title_page: Poland's clash of values in presidential election - BBC News
maintext: If Andrzej Duda gets 50% of the vote on Sunday, he will win - but he is unlikely to achieve that. If the mayor of Warsaw attracts as much support as the opinion polls suggest, then Mr Trzaskowski will take part in a run-off that is currently too close to call.
